			<tr>
				<td><font face="verdana" size="1">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="/quests/default.asp">Quests</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="default.asp?land=1471">Lesser Faydark</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline3.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<b>Ghast Heart (Felwithe Cleric Quest)</b><br><br>
				</td>
			</tr>
				
			<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Ghast Heart (Felwithe Cleric Quest)</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=405800"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:leskiwj@hotmail.com">SgtSarros</a> | 
		                        4/10/2001 6:01:39 PM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">In Felwithe when i turned in the bone chips.. I saw a new message I had noticed before. Saying I am ready to become a Initiate Of Tunare. when entering those 3 keywords they say that the people who created the Skeletons have created a new creature called a Ghast, and thy can be found at the Lesser Faydark. The quest is to return four Ghast hearts to Yeoyarn Bronzeleaf.<BR>
<BR>
I have checked this area out with my level 10 ranger, and had a level 30 ranger check for me a few times.. but not find a single Ghast in there. It is possible that this quest is not completable at this time.. tho two or three people HAVE reported seeing a Ghast, but never killed one.<BR>
<BR>

			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
			</tr>
